<ab><lb n="1"/> <w lemma="ὁ">ἡ</w> <w lemma="σορός">σορὸς</w> <w lemma="καί"><orig reg="καὶ">κὲ</orig></w> <w lemma="ὁ">ὁ</w> <w lemma="τόπος">τόπος</w> <w lemma="εἰμί">ἐστιν</w> <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Μᾶρκος"><expan><abbr>Μ</abbr><ex>άρκου</ex></expan></name> <name nymRef="#Αὐρήλιος"><expan><abbr>Αὐρ</abbr><ex>ηλίου</ex></expan></name><name nymRef="#Μένανδρος">Μενάνδρου</name> <w lemma="ὁ">τοῦ</w> <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Ἀγαπωμενός">Ἀγα<lb n="2" break="no"/>πωμενοῦ</name>  <lb n="3"/> <w lemma="ὁ">τοῦ</w> <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Φημιδης">Φημι<lb n="4" break="no"/>δου</name></persName></persName></persName><lb n="5"/> <w lemma="ζάω">Ζῶσιν</w></ab>
</div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>The tomb and the space for it belong to M. Aurelius Menandros son of Agapomenos son of Phemidos. They are alive.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The inscription appears to be secondary to the sarcophagus.</p>
         </div>
